    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@bobylito here's an example of how I would use `rootTag`:\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst Template = 'instantsearch.js/es/components/Template.js';\r\n\r\nclass HitsTable extends React.Component {\r\n  renderWithResults() {\r\n    const renderedHits = map(this.props.hits, (hit, position) => {\r\n      const data = {\r\n        ...hit,\r\n        __hitIndex: position,\r\n      };\r\n      return (\r\n        <Template\r\n          data={data}\r\n          key={data.objectID}\r\n          rootProps={{ className: this.props.cssClasses.item }}\r\n          rootTag=\"tr\"\r\n          templateKey=\"item\"\r\n          {...this.props.templateProps}\r\n        />\r\n      );\r\n    });\r\n\r\n    return <table className={this.props.cssClasses.root}>{renderedHits}</table>;\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThere really isn't an alternative - aside from duplicating the `Template` component with my own that allows this, or using a widget that renders a table as divs.",
    "created_at": "2017-11-20T12:53:43Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2525#issuecomment-345687217",
